rComments: Marina is one of the smartest and most talented professors Ive ever met. It was a pleasure to take her course. Highly recommend her.

Very knowledgeable prof (in her specialization). However she has poor time management skills. She speaks way too quietly despite the multiple times students have asked her to speak up. Does not respond to emails AT ALL. Very boring lectures but every second is filled with lots of information. All in all, not a bad prof but not the best either.

Best French professor ever! She is so helpful, nice and also caring for her students.  She shows great dedication for her students and the class is really enjoyable! Would totally recommend taking that class with her!

Marina is an extremely helpful prof, she's always free at office hours and takes the time to go over content to make sure students understand. Gives very helpful examples to help students understand concepts. Lectures cover lots of info, but she often stays at least half an hour after class to help. Very nice, and can relate to students, flexible.
